**Reference**: `history/planv0.md` — grep for these type names throughout the document to see usage patterns.

### Implementation Notes
```rust
// ids.rs — macro-generate newtypes for type safety
macro_rules! typed_id {
    ($name:ident, $inner:ty) => {
        #[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash, Serialize, Deserialize)]
        pub struct $name(pub $inner);
        impl From<$inner> for $name { fn from(v: $inner) -> Self { Self(v) } }
    };
}

typed_id!(LayerId, u16);
typed_id!(ExpertId, u16);
typed_id!(BudgetSlotId, u16);

// String-wrapped ids for named entities
macro_rules! string_id {
    ($name:ident) => {
        #[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Hash, Serialize, Deserialize)]
        pub struct $name(pub String);
    };
}

string_id!(TargetProfileId);
string_id!(CompileProfileId);
string_id!(TargetFamilyId);
string_id!(CheckpointId);
string_id!(WorkloadId);
```

- Keep it minimal — just newtypes + derives + basic impls.
- Hash256: include `Display` (hex), `FromStr`, `as_bytes()`, `from_bytes()`.
- ByteCost: implement Add, Sub, Display, Ord for comparison.

