## Agent Instructions

**Target crate(s)**: `gbf-model` (trait + spec), `gbf-artifact` (lands SequenceSemanticsSpec in ArtifactCore).
**Target file(s)**: `gbf-model/src/sequence/mod.rs` (new), `gbf-model/src/sequence/spec.rs` (new), `gbf-artifact/src/core/sequence.rs` (extend).

**Reference**: `history/planv0.md` — search "SequenceSemanticsSpec", "SequenceBlock", "state semantics", "ArtifactCore". Also F12 design notes on bd-144.

### Implementation Notes

Define the spec in `gbf-model`:

```rust
pub enum SequenceSemanticsSpec {
    LinearState {
        state_bytes_per_layer: u16,
    },
    BoundedKv {
        max_context: u16,
        kv_bytes_per_token: u16,
    },
}

pub struct SequenceStateSize {
    pub bytes_per_layer: u32,
    pub bytes_per_token: u16,    // 0 for LinearState
    pub fixed_overhead: u16,
}

pub trait SequenceBlock {
    type Backend: ::burn::backend::Backend;
    fn forward(
        &self,
        x: ::burn::tensor::Tensor<Self::Backend, 3>,
        state: &mut SequenceState<Self::Backend>,
    ) -> ::burn::tensor::Tensor<Self::Backend, 3>;
    fn state_init(&self) -> SequenceState<Self::Backend>;
    fn state_size(&self) -> SequenceStateSize;
    fn export_facts(&self) -> SequenceExportFacts;
}

pub struct SequenceExportFacts {
    pub spec: SequenceSemanticsSpec,
    pub measured_state_size: SequenceStateSize,
    /// Hooks consumed by ExportVisitor to populate ArtifactCore.
    pub canonical_tensor_handles: Vec<CanonicalTensorHandle>,
}
```

Then in `gbf-artifact`:
- Add `pub sequence_semantics: SequenceSemanticsSpec` to `ArtifactCore` (or its `ArtifactSemanticPayload`, depending on how the core is structured).
- Adding this changes `ArtifactCore` content hash semantics — that is correct; LinearState and BoundedKv artifacts MUST have distinct semantic hashes.

Add a `SequenceSemanticsRef` reference type to `gbf-policy` for use in `CompileProfile.sequence_state` (T11.2):

```rust
pub enum SequenceSemanticsRef {
    Unspecified,
    LinearState,
    BoundedKv,
}
```

`Unspecified` is the BringUp default until production profiles are defined.

### Acceptance Criteria

```bash
cargo check -p gbf-model                                   # Compiles
cargo check -p gbf-artifact                                # Compiles
cargo test -p gbf-model -- sequence::spec                   # Spec round-trips through serde
cargo test -p gbf-artifact -- core::sequence_semantics      # ArtifactCore carries sequence_semantics
cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings                     # No warnings
# Verify: SequenceBlock trait can be implemented (compile a minimal impl in a test)
# Verify: SequenceExportFacts is populated by ExportVisitor (T1.6) — leave a TODO if blocked
# Verify: Two ArtifactCores with different SequenceSemanticsSpec have different content hashes
```

### Constitution Checkpoints

- §I.1: `SequenceSemanticsSpec` enum + `SequenceBlock` trait make it impossible to produce a model whose sequence semantics are unrecorded.
- §VI.1: SequenceSemanticsSpec is in `gbf-model` (model semantics) and referenced from `gbf-artifact`; not duplicated.
- §III.1: Variant differences become a compile error at every dispatch site that doesn't handle both.
